# YouTube Fantasy Basketball Newsletter

## Project Overview
Python CLI tool that monitors YouTube channels via RSS, extracts transcripts, analyzes with Gemini, and emails fantasy basketball player recommendation newsletters.

## Architecture
- `src/yt_newsletter/monitor.py` — CLI application with all pipeline logic
- Root `monitor.py` — shim so `python monitor.py …` works without `pip install -e .`
- `config.json` — User credentials and channel list (gitignored, created via `yt-newsletter init` or `python -m yt_newsletter init`)
- `state.json` — Tracks which videos have been processed (gitignored)
- `history.json` — Stores all analyses for weekly recap aggregation (gitignored)

## Key Commands
- `yt-newsletter init` (or `python -m yt_newsletter init`) — Create default config.json
- `yt-newsletter test <youtube-url>` — Test full pipeline on any existing video
- `yt-newsletter add-channel <name> <channel_id>` — Add a channel to monitor
- `yt-newsletter monitor` — Start polling loop (every 90 seconds)
- `yt-newsletter recap` — Send weekly recap email

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.10+
- `feedparser` — YouTube RSS parsing
- `youtube-transcript-api` — Transcript extraction (no API key needed)
- `google-generativeai` — Gemini API client (`import google.generativeai`)
- Gmail SMTP — Email delivery
- No database, all state is JSON files

## Design Decisions
- RSS over YouTube Data API: free, no quota, faster detection (2-5 min)
- Packaged under `src/yt_newsletter/`; config/state files stay at repo root
- Gemini 2.5 Flash: cheapest model that handles transcript analysis well (~$0.01/video)
- JSON output from Gemini: structured prompt requests raw JSON, stripped of markdown fences

## Config Requirements
- `gemini_api_key`: from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
- `email_app_password`: Gmail App Password (NOT regular password), from https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
- Channel IDs: find via page source on YouTube channel page, search for `channel_id`

## When Modifying
- The Gemini prompt is in `ANALYSIS_PROMPT` — edit categories there if adding new recommendation types
- Player scoring weights for weekly recap are in `SCORE_MAP` inside `build_weekly_recap_html()`
- To add a new sport, duplicate the prompt and adjust player extraction logic
- Email HTML is inline in `build_email_html()` and `build_weekly_recap_html()`
